<LP>
   In your Jan. 20 article "Mexico Guards Its Precious Oil
Business," there are serious discrepancies, i.e., "Yankee
interlopers, who, after all, took oil-rich Texas from Mexico
in 1848."
   Texas took itself from Mexico on April 21, 1836, defeating
Gen. Antonio Lopez de Santa Anna in the 20-minute Battle of
San Jacinto, as every third-grader in Texas could tell you --
or could have in 1927, anyway.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   And Texans are not Yankees.
   <ORGANIZATION>Allen T. Smith
   El Paso</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Texas</LOCATION>
</TEXT>
